PARENTS/GUARDIANS: We would like to invite you to our Russell High School Parent-Teacher Welcome on Monday (8/31) and Tuesday (9/1). You may either attend in-person or virtually. Please see the details below.

A general presentation about what to expect or see this year, how the learning guides will work, and how synchronous and asynchronous offerings will happen.

In-person attendees will enter by the gym. After the presentation, parents may walk down our halls to see school-wide improvements and ask teachers questions. They will be directed to exit through the west doors.

Karly Little from Barton will be available on Monday, August 31 from 12:00-2:30 and 3:30-4:30 via Zoom to assist any students needing to enroll in Barton classes. Please make sure you have been admitted to Barton prior to attending the Zoom meeting.

Please see attached link for the schedule: https://5il.co/kff6

post_text: If you’ve not filled out the census yet please be sure to do so soon. Every single person counts ☺️
shared_text:
Dane G. Hansen Foundation
June 23 at 10:26 AM ·

Federal funds that pay for road construction, school programs, healthcare needs and a variety of other services that make the quality of life better in Northwest Kansas are distributed on the basis of census results. That's just one important reason everyone who lives here needs to be counted in the 2020 U.S. Census! Please make sure your rural friends and neighbors respond. They can do it by phone at 1-844-330-2020, online at 2020census.gov or through the mail.

More than 70 percent of Kansans responded to the census in 2010 before census takers began their work. The state's current response rate is 65.4 percent. After you've responded, think of five people who you could call and remind or offer assistance to and make sure they respond as well. Let's all do our part to bring that number up! #CallForTheCount #KansasCounts

post_text:
USD 407 Community and Students:
The world seeks us to pay attention to some details in recent weeks that perhaps we’ve not. With the turmoil that has boiled up from prejudice and racism in the society at large, USD 407 takes a moment to view these things reflectively and with compassion.
USD 407 believes in personal wellbeing and safety at all schools. We know that we cannot police or create a perfect environment, but our policies and procedures promote and set a standard of equality in our hallways, classrooms, and the opportunities that school offers. Staff, students, visitors, leaders, and families are inclusively welcomed regardless of one’s background. We care about both the present and the potential of USD 407 students. We wish for anyone who comes to our schools to feel confident and safe as they enjoy our schools and activities.

post_text: We are saddened to hear of the passing of our outstanding Bronco Jaide Lawson, Class of 2020, on May 13. Russell High School will offer counseling to all students, staff, and family who need individual support during this time on Thursday, May 14, from 2:00 - 4:00 & Friday, May 15, 10:00 AM - Noon @ Shaffer Field concession stand/ courtyard. Please remain aware of social distancing for safety during this time; RHS and USD staff will be doing the same. Our team will be flexible to help beyond the time frames as requested by students. #TeamJaide
shared_text:
Team Jaide
May 13 at 8:39 PM ·

My heart is broken!!!!
Fly high my Jaide...My heart and soul will never be the same without you here.
I will always keep you in my heart 💔💔💔
Forever my person and always my best friend
#TeamJaide #BestHumanIEverKnew #TooGoodForEarth #BeFreeMyJaide

Community: If you are self or mandated quarantine/ isolation in the USD 407 boundaries, we can help. If you have children age 1-18 and wish to have the grab n go meals delivered to your home, we can help you!
Email each child’s name & age, with your delivery address to sswayne@usd407.org. Please only request this service for isolation & quarantine as we don’t have the time or resources for home delivery for all children; our public parks pick up is linked here.
